 {"id":"beads_rust-nh5h","title":"Implement Theme with semantic colors and styles","description":"# Task: Implement Theme

## What to Do
Create the Theme struct that EXTENDS the existing color patterns in `src/format/text.rs`.

## File to Create
`src/format/theme.rs` (NOT src/output/theme.rs)

## CRITICAL: Reuse Existing Color Patterns
The codebase already defines colors in `src/format/text.rs`:
- Status colors: green (open) → yellow (in_progress) → red (blocked) → gray (closed)
- Priority colors: red+bold (P0) → red → yellow → gray
- Type colors: task (cyan), bug (red), feature (green), epic (magenta)
- Icons: ○ ◐ ● ❄ ✓ ✗ 📌

**DO NOT DUPLICATE** - import and extend these patterns.

## Design Philosophy
The theme provides SEMANTIC colors - colors that have meaning in context:
- Success: green (aligns with open/completed)
- Error: red (aligns with blocked/bug)
- Warning: yellow (aligns with in_progress)
- Info: cyan (aligns with task type)
- Accent: magenta (aligns with epic type)

## Implementation

```rust
//! Theme definitions for beads_rust CLI styling.
//!
//! EXTENDS existing color patterns from text.rs - do not duplicate!

use rich_rust::Style;
use crate::model::{Status, Priority, IssueType};

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct Theme {
    pub success: Style,     // Green - matches open status
    pub error: Style,       // Red - matches blocked/bug
    pub warning: Style,     // Yellow - matches in_progress
    pub info: Style,        // Cyan - matches task type
    pub dimmed: Style,      // Gray - matches closed/deferred
    pub accent: Style,      // Magenta - matches epic
    pub highlight: Style,   // Bold white
    pub issue_id: Style,
    pub issue_title: Style,
}

impl Theme {
    pub fn status_style(&self, status: Status) -> Style;
    pub fn priority_style(&self, priority: Priority) -> Style;
    pub fn type_style(&self, issue_type: IssueType) -> Style;
    pub fn status_icon(&self, status: Status) -> &'static str;
}
```

## Consistency Check
The Theme MUST produce visually consistent output with existing text.rs functions.

## CRITICAL: Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests Location
`tests/format/theme_tests.rs`

### Required Test Cases

```rust
use beads_rust::format::Theme;
use beads_rust::model::{Status, Priority, IssueType};
use tracing::{info, debug};

fn init_test_logging() {
    let _ = tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        .with_test_writer()
        .with_env_filter("debug")
        .try_init();
}

// Status Style Tests

#[test]
fn test_status_style_open_is_green() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Open status should be green");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.status_style(Status::Open);

    // Verify style contains green color
    assert!(style.has_fg_color());
    debug!("Open status style: {:?}", style);
    info!("PASSED: Open status is green");
}

#[test]
fn test_status_style_in_progress_is_yellow() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: InProgress status should be yellow");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.status_style(Status::InProgress);

    assert!(style.has_fg_color());
    info!("PASSED: InProgress status is yellow");
}

#[test]
fn test_status_style_blocked_is_red() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Blocked status should be red");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.status_style(Status::Blocked);

    assert!(style.has_fg_color());
    info!("PASSED: Blocked status is red");
}

#[test]
fn test_status_style_closed_is_dimmed() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Closed status should be dimmed");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.status_style(Status::Closed);

    // Closed should be gray/dimmed
    info!("PASSED: Closed status is dimmed");
}

// Priority Style Tests

#[test]
fn test_priority_style_p0_is_red_bold() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: P0 priority should be red and bold");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.priority_style(Priority::P0);

    assert!(style.is_bold());
    info!("PASSED: P0 is red bold");
}

#[test]
fn test_priority_heat_map_ordering() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Priority heat map: P0 > P1 > P2 > P3");

    let theme = Theme::default();

    // P0 should be boldest/most urgent
    let p0 = theme.priority_style(Priority::P0);
    let p1 = theme.priority_style(Priority::P1);
    let p2 = theme.priority_style(Priority::P2);
    let p3 = theme.priority_style(Priority::P3);

    assert!(p0.is_bold());  // P0 is bold
    assert!(!p1.is_bold()); // P1 is not bold

    info!("PASSED: Priority heat map ordering");
}

// Type Style Tests

#[test]
fn test_type_style_bug_is_red() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Bug type should be red");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.type_style(IssueType::Bug);

    // Bug should be same as error color
    info!("PASSED: Bug type is red");
}

#[test]
fn test_type_style_epic_is_accent() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Epic type should be accent color");

    let theme = Theme::default();
    let style = theme.type_style(IssueType::Epic);

    info!("PASSED: Epic type is accent");
}

// Icon Tests

#[test]
fn test_status_icons_are_correct() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Status icons should match text.rs");

    let theme = Theme::default();

    assert_eq!(theme.status_icon(Status::Open), "○");
    assert_eq!(theme.status_icon(Status::InProgress), "◐");
    assert_eq!(theme.status_icon(Status::Blocked), "●");
    assert_eq!(theme.status_icon(Status::Closed), "✓");
    assert_eq!(theme.status_icon(Status::Deferred), "❄");

    info!("PASSED: All status icons correct");
}

// Consistency Tests with text.rs

#[test]
fn test_theme_matches_text_rs_colors() {
    init_test_logging();
    info!("TEST: Theme colors must match text.rs patterns");

    // This test should import both Theme and text.rs formatters
    // and verify they produce consistent colors

    // Example: format_status(Status::Open) should produce same
    // visual color as theme.status_style(Status::Open)

    info!("PASSED: Theme matches text.rs colors");
}
```

